-- Egypt's Food Industries to Build $210 Million Sugar Refinery, Al Mal Says
-- Ahmed A Namatalla
-- 2010-06-21T06:35:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-21/egypt-s-food-industries-to-build-210-million-sugar-refinery-al-mal-says.html

          
          
             Egypt’s state-run Food Industries
Holding Co. will build a 1.2 billion Egyptian pound ($210
million) sugar refinery with international investors, Al Mal
reported today, citing the company’s chairman Ahmed El Rokayebi.  
 The Food Industries Holding Co. has received offers from
German and Japanese investors to build the sugar refinery, in
which it will have a 40 percent stake, the Cairo-based business
newspaper said.  
 Construction will begin in January and take two years, it
said. The refinery will be financed through bank loans, the
newspaper said.  
